  <head>
    <title>Group</title>
    <abstract>
      <para>Group memberships are for organizations using Swarm in-house
        by one or more users.</para></abstract>
  </head>
  
  <itemizedlist>
    
    <listitem><formalpara><title>Elite</title><para> Elite members are
          organizations that wish to sponsor the Swarm Development
          Group and offer strong direction to the development of the
          Swarm Simulation System.</para></formalpara></listitem>
    
    <listitem><formalpara><title>Charter<footnote> <para> Charter
              memberships may not be available after the inaugural
              year. </para>
          </footnote>
        </title> <para> Charter members are organizations that would
          like to be instrumental in the founding of the Swarm
          Development Group.</para></formalpara></listitem>
    
    <listitem><formalpara><title>Corporate</title><para> Corporate
          members generally represent corporations.</para></formalpara>
    </listitem>
    
    <listitem><formalpara><title>Government</title><para>
          Government members generally represent government
          agencies.</para></formalpara></listitem>
    
    <listitem><formalpara><title>University</title><para>
          University members generally represent a university.</para></formalpara></listitem>
    
  </itemizedlist>

